\begin{verbatim}
AutoEMASdofProblem(H, freq; type, dpi, method)
\end{verbatim}
Structure containing the input data for automatic experimental modal analysis using Sdof methods

\textbf{Fields}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{H::Array\{Complex, 3\}}: Frequency response function matrix


\item \texttt{freq::AbstractRange}: Frequency vector [Hz]


\item \texttt{type::Symbol}: Type of FRF used to extract the natural frequencies and damping ratios

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{:dis}: Admittance (default)


\item \texttt{:vel}: Mobility


\item \texttt{:acc}: Accelerance

\end{itemize}

\item \texttt{dpi::Vector\{Int\}}: Driving point indices - default = [1, 1]

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{dpi[1]}: Driving point index on the measurement mesh


\item \texttt{dpi[2]}: Driving point index on the excitation mesh

\end{itemize}

\item \texttt{method::SdofModalExtraction}: Method to extract the natural frequencies and damping ratios

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{PeakPicking}: Peak picking method (default)


\item \texttt{CircleFit}: Circle fitting method


\item \texttt{LSFit}: Least squares fitting method

\end{itemize}
\end{itemize}

\begin{verbatim}
EMASolution(fn, ξn, ϕn)
\end{verbatim}
Structure containing the solution of the automatic experimental modal analysis using Sdof methods

\textbf{Fields}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{f}: Natural frequencies


\item \texttt{xi}: Damping ratios


\item \texttt{ms}: Mode shapes

\end{itemize}

\begin{verbatim}
freq_extraction(freq, H, method::SdofModalExtraction; type = :dis)
\end{verbatim}
Extract natural frequencies and damping ratios from the Bode diagram fitting method

\textbf{Inputs}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{freq}: Frequency vector


\item \texttt{H}: Frequency response function


\item \texttt{method}: Method to extract the natural frequencies and damping ratios

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{PeakPicking}: Peak picking method (default)


\item \texttt{CircleFit}: Circle fitting method


\item \texttt{LSFit}: Least squares fitting method

\end{itemize}

\item \texttt{type}: Type of FRF used to extract the natural frequencies and damping ratios

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{:dis}: Admittance (default)


\item \texttt{:vel}: Mobility


\item \texttt{:acc}: Accelerance

\end{itemize}
\end{itemize}
\textbf{Outputs}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{fn}: Natural frequencies


\item \texttt{ξn}: Damping ratios

\end{itemize}
\textbf{Note} It is supposed that \texttt{H} is a row or a column of the FRF, meaning that H is a Vector

\begin{verbatim}
modeshape_extraction(freq, H, fn, ξn, dpi; type = :dis)
\end{verbatim}
Extract mode shapes using Sdof approximation

\textbf{Inputs}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{freq}: Frequency vector


\item \texttt{H}: Frequency response function


\item \texttt{fn}: Natural frequencies


\item \texttt{ξn}: Damping ratios


\item \texttt{dpi}: Driving point indices - default = [1, 1]

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{dpi[1]}: Driving point index on the measurement mesh


\item \texttt{dpi[2]}: Driving point index on the excitation mesh

\end{itemize}

\item \texttt{type}: Type of FRF used to extract the natural frequencies and damping ratios

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{:dis}: Admittance (default)


\item \texttt{:vel}: Mobility


\item \texttt{:acc}: Accelerance

\end{itemize}
\end{itemize}
\textbf{Output}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{ϕn}: Mode shapes

\end{itemize}
\textbf{Note} If the number of measurement points is less than the number of excitation points, the mode shapes are estimated at the excitation points (roving hammer test). Otherwise, the mode shapes are estimated at the measurement points (roving accelerometer test).

\begin{verbatim}
solve(prob::AutoEMASdofProblem)
\end{verbatim}
Solve automatically experimental modal analysis problem using Sdof methods

\textbf{Inputs}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{prob}: Structure containing the input data for automatic experimental modal analysis using Sdof methods

\end{itemize}
\textbf{Outputs}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{sol}: Solution of problem:

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{f}: Natural frequencies


\item \texttt{xi}: Damping ratios


\item \texttt{ms}: Mode shapes

\end{itemize}
\end{itemize}
